The paper deals with motion estimation and mapping for autonomous mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses stereo cameras and combines feature-based matching with semi-dense direct image alignment, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning for depth estimation, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the approach for handling large inter-frame motion and illumination changes, which could be relevant to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
